        <p> The red potion is a staple in traditional RPG gaming, appearing in such titles as <em> The Legend of Zelda </em> and <em Minecraft </em>.
        It usually acts to replenish the health of a character! </p>

        <h2> Ingredients (serves 2-3)</h2>
        <p>235ml cranberry juice <br> 55g frozen cherries
          <br> 60g frozen raspberries <br> 40g cubed watermelon
          <br> frozen mango chunks <br> 1 teaspoon ginger
          <br> (optional) red food colouring </p>

        <h3> Method </h3>
        <ol>
          <li> Put all of the ingredients into a blender and blend until smooth </li>
          <li> Pour into a suitable bottle and enjoy! </li>
        </ol>

        <h4> Nutritional info </h4>
        <p> This recipe is a mix of differing fruits known for their vitamin content and antioxident properties. Ginger is known
          to ease muscle ache and act as an anti-inflammatory, creating a potion that will certainly replenish your health! </p>

        <h5> Alternatives </h5>
        <p> To create a green potion, use green jelly and limeade, or switch out food colouring!</p>
